    <pw:title>
      Simplicity as a Design Goal
    </pw:title>
    <pw:file-name>
      simplicity_as_a_design_goal
    </pw:file-name>
    <pw:body>
      <p>
        Simplicity goes beyond a term like 'good user interface,' which has become so broad, it has little clear meaning. Simplicity is a goal with precision. <em>Simplicity</em> means streamlining, pruning clutter, cleaning up presentation, and improving the initial experience with a product. But Simplicity is more than just making a cute product for technophobes. Simplicity streamlines and optimizes use, as well.
      </p>
